com.opengamma.strata.product

Interface Expandable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the expanded form
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CdsProduct, FixedCouponBondProduct, FraProduct, FxNdfProduct, FxSingleProduct, FxSwapProduct, FxVanillaOptionProduct, IborFixingDepositProduct, SwapProduct, SwaptionProduct, TermDepositProduct
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Cds, ExpandedCds, ExpandedFixedCouponBond, ExpandedFra, ExpandedFxNdf, ExpandedFxSingle, ExpandedFxSwap, ExpandedIborFixingDeposit, ExpandedSwap, ExpandedSwaption, ExpandedTermDeposit, FixedCouponBond, Fra, FxNdf, FxSingle, FxSwap, FxVanillaOption, IborFixingDeposit, Swap, Swaption, TermDeposit

    public interface Expandable<T>
    An object that can be expanded for pricing.

    Interface marking those objects that can be expanded for pricing.

    The expanded form of an object has certain conversions performed ready for pricing. In this form, the holiday calendar rules have been applied, with dates being adjusted to valid business days. If the holiday calendar changes, then the expanded form may no longer be accurate. Care must be taken when placing the expanded form in a cache or persistence layer.

    Implementations must be immutable and thread-safe beans.

    • Method Detail

      • expand

        T expand()
        Expands this Object.

        This converts the object implementing this interface to the equivalent expanded form. Conversion must not be lossy.

        Returns:
        the expanded form of this object
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if unable to expand due to an invalid definition
